728626f-a.title: Richmond: Broadway - Clove Road
728626f-a.text:
Broadway (right), north from its junction with Clove Road,
showing the Point House (center) of which E.H. Chose was the owner
in 1898 and Anna Krohn in 1907, Visible on the left is part of
St. Peters cemetery.
January 9, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

729781f-a.title: Richmond: Tyler Street - Clove Road
729781f-a.text:
Tyler treet, north side, east of Clove Road,
showing the Tyler H use. It was built in 1835 by Mrs.
Elisa Racey and derives its name from having been owned
by Mrs. Julia Tyler, widow of Presiuent Tyler, from 1868
to 1878.
May 16, 1932
P. L. Sperr
